videos.description: Lamar Jackson rushes 10 yards up the middle for a touchdown giving Louisville an early 7-0 lead over Kentucky. The TD was Jackson's 20th rushing score of the season.
videos.headline: Jackson cruises up the middle for TD

videos.description: Kentucky RB Stanley Williams burst through a hole and 36 yards to the end zone to give the Wildcats a 14-7 lead over Louisville.
videos.headline: Kentucky's Stanley Williams bursts 36 yards for TD

videos.description: Lamar Jackson finds Reggie Bonnafon wide open in the corner of the end zone for an 18-yard touchdown to tie up Louisville's game with Kentucky 14-14.
videos.headline: Jackson connects with Bonnafon for 18-yard TD

videos.description: Jojo Kemp pass intercepted Trumaine Washington return for 18 yds to the Kent 48
videos.headline: Louisville gets the interception on the tipped ball

videos.headline: Jackson shuffles pass to Hikutini for TD

videos.description: Kentucky QB Stephen Johnson launches his second touchdown of the game against Louisville, a 63-yard strike to Garrett Johnson.
videos.headline: Johnson finds Johnson for second long TD of game

videos.description: Kentucky head coach Mark Stoopes happy with the big plays his offense got in the 1st half

videos.headline: S. Johnson gets his own deflection and runs it for a 1st down

videos.description: Kentucky lines up in wildcat formation and RB Benny Snell Jr.  rushes 18 yards for a touchdown giving the Wildcats a 28-24 lead over Louisville.
videos.headline: Kentucky uses wildcat formation to take lead

videos.description: Lamar Jackson breaks through Kentucky's defensive line and races downfield 61 yards into the red zone, which leads to a short touchdown run from Jeremy Smith.
videos.headline: Jackson's 61-yard run sets up Louisville score

videos.description: Kentucky QB Stephen Johnson lobs a pass up for Dorian Baker, who comes down with a great 35-yard touchdown catch to give the Wildcats the lead over Louisville.
videos.headline: Kentucky takes lead on fantastic 35-yard TD grab

videos.headline: Kentucky picks off Lamar Jackson... again

videos.headline: Kentucky gets it done on the road
